      <block class="online_lead_paragraph">
        <p>On Monday, Michelangelo's David is scheduled for an especially thorough scrubbing at the Galleria dell'Accademia in Florence.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Seven months is an awfully long bath, but then David went more than a century without one. So on Monday, Michelangelo's famous sculpture is scheduled for an especially thorough scrubbing at the Galleria dell'Accademia in Florence that will probably last until the end of March.</p>
        <p>It will be the first hygienic renaissance for the Renaissance masterpiece since 1873, and will cost considerably more than an afternoon at Elizabeth Arden. Restorers have put the price at about $150,000. They have also decided not to give the nude statue any privacy for its ablutions. Visitors to the gallery can watch the process.</p>
      </block>
